-- TAKE A LOOK-Malaysia jet debris hunts steps up; detectors arrive
-- 
-- Wed Mar 26, 2014 06:29AM EDT
-- None



March 26 (Reuters) -    U.S. equipment designed to detect black box signals arrived in Australia as searchers stepped up efforts to find some trace of a Malaysian airliner, with 239 people aboard, that is thought to have crashed 18 days ago thousands of miles off course in the Indian Ocean.

